label.value: MYCN Gene Copy Number/Chromosome 2 Copy Number in Tissue by FISH

value.value: A quantitative fluorescent in situ hybridization-based procedure that measures the number of copies of the MYCN gene per the number of copies of chromosome 2 in a tissue specimen.

label.value: 1p/1q Chromosome Deletion [Number Ratio] in Tissue by FISH

label.value: Chemical Interference

value.value: A type of footprinting technique used to define the location of protein-nucleic acid contacts at the base pair level in nucleic acids.  It utilizes nucleic acids treated with a chemical in such a way that only a fraction of the nucleotides are chemically modified.  The chemically modified nucleotides that interfere with protein-nucleic acid complex formation can be identified by fragmentation and electrophoretic analysis of the DNA isolated from the complexes.
